                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-10-23</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I too am a heterosexual man who loves this movie. I didn't see it for the first time until years after it left theaters. It never appealed to me before then. I thought "Oh my. A very old Clint Eastwood and tear jerking Meryl Streep are doing the film version of a very over publicized book." Ok, so it happend to be on cable one early morning and I came across it. I started watching the first 5 minutes and by the end I cried so many tears that I couldn't believe it... and I don't cry much at all. <P>This movie is beautiful.. from the way it's shot, to the genuine and heartfelt performances of Clint and Streep. This movie blew me away. This movie is about love, hope, and sacrifice. Unbelievable. Ignore those who cast bad opinions of this flick. This movie is not for the lover of fast paced, action movies. They won't "get it." By the way, 'ol Dirty Harry's work with the musical score is sensational. Listen to "Doe Eyes" and tell me it doesn't fill you up!<P>Yes, on paper this movie is about a married woman's affair with another man. However, this is not the heart of the story. Meryl's character came to America in the hopes of a new and exciting life only to find herself on a farm in East Bumbleland, Iowa doing nothing but household chores day in and day out, married to a husband who isn't even remotely in tune with his emotions.. not to mention her kids who weren't exactly the most loving people in the world either. This movie is about hope and that the dream of finding that special someone still exists, even years later. This movie does not justify extra-marital affairs. Anyone who thinks so is simply narrow minded. I won't give away the ending to those who haven't seen it but I can tell you that if the movie had a different outcome, some of the "affair" arguments may have been able to hold water... alas.. they don't.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The best love story of all time</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
